                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1337: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Horn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-13T10:00:00-03:50"
                            >August 13, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. My 69, July 3, 1 p.m., reporting Argentina’s suggestion concerning policing
                    of Chaco. I have just learned that about 2 weeks ago this suggestion was turned
                    down by the Paraguayan Government. It maintained Bolivian troops are now in
                    actual possession of Paraguayan territory. It was intimated that if the troops
                    withdrew to less advanced positions that perhaps more favorable consideration
                    could later on be given the suggestion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
